caption:
Donut uplift and fat grafting to correct breast implant complications - result at 3 months.

This lady had 2 previous augmentations by a different surgeon.

Since her last surgery, her breast tissue had fallen over the implants (waterfall effect), with a low nipple position and poor contour in the upper pole/cleavage area (arrow).

These problems are common when a breast uplift is not performed in the first instance when it is required.

Her aim was to obtain a nipple lift avoiding extensive scarring and without exchanging the implants. This was achieved with a periareolar(donut) lift using a permanent Gore-tex suture. At the same time a fat grafting procedure has successfully addressed the upper pole and clevage area irregularities(arrow) ðŸŽ¯

Fat grafting not only improves the breast shape but also rejuvenates the skin, giving the breasts a more youthful appearance. 

Abdominal lipo was an additional bonus!

caption:
Fibula flap for mandible reconstruction - Graphic content!

Fibula flap is the workhorse flap in Head&Neck bony reconstruction.

It is usually raised as a chimeric flap with 1 or 2 skin paddles and additional muscle (FHL or soleus).

Traditionally we were used to do the osteotomies "free hand" after disconnecting the flap from the leg.

With the introduction of the CAD/CAM technology and pre-planning of the reconstruction, it is now possible to perform the osteotomies and the plating on the leg, with the flap still attached on its pedicle.(slide to picture 2).

Preplaning not only saves time but also provides a more accurate reconstruction with better functional outcomes.

A pre-operative leg CT Angiogram is recommended to avoid intra-operative surprises when a Peroneal Magna artery is present (pic 3) -5% incidence. If present, the peroneal Magna artery is the only artery supplying the foot and therefore another bone flap should be used.

caption:
Excision and reconstruction of an ear SCC.

Some types of skin cancer are particularly aggressive and require relatively urgent treatment. Thankfully, we are still able to offer such treatment in the NHS despite the current Covid disruption.

Here is a case of a Sqamous cell carcinoma (SCC) of the ear, which was removed and reconstructed with a helical rim advancement (or Antia - Buch) flap.

This particular type of skin cancer can aggressively grow to the entire ear and also spread into and neck nodes. 
This patient underwent early excision with complete clearance. With careful planning and local flap reconstruction the anatomy of the ear was preserved and the scars are barely visble.

caption:
Breast uplift with autoaugmentation - no implants âœ…. Early result at 2 weeks.

Auto-augmentation is an uplift technique, which uses the existing breast tissue to increase upper pole fullness, and create a perkier breast with no need for implantsðŸŽ¯

It consists of "splitting" the breast into 2 parts - Superior and inferior. The inferior breast part, based on the inferior pedicle, acts as an implant. It enhances the upper breast by being moved into a pocket created higher on the chest (pic 2). The superior part allows the nipple to be lifted into it's new position. A small reduction is also possible if needed. The breast is finally shaped with several layers of dissolvable stitches.

As for every other technique in plastic surgery, breast auto-augmentation requires an in depth understanding of the blood supply. â˜Žï¸�02071778118 or follow the link on bio to book an appointment.

How long is recovery from Breast Reduction?

Nerve weakness - #neuropraxia - is always feared by patients and #surgeons in #faceliftsurgery but if caused by swelling or tightness the effect is always temporary. Iâ€™ll explain today how and why it happens. Our nerves are basically data cables from the brain ðŸ§  or spinal cord to our muscles. ðŸ’ªðŸ�¼ We think smile and our #facialmuscles move. To work, nerves need a blood supply which runs on the outside of the cable. Anything that affects that (swelling, traction, tightness) causes a data block in the cable despite the cable being physically fine. It takes a few weeks for the data to run freely through the cable again. Itâ€™s that simple ðŸ‘�ðŸ�».
.
And that can be a sweaty time ðŸ˜“ for patients as they await the inevitable but fear the worst.
.
Thatâ€™s the beauty of #deepplanefacelift surgery from my own experience is neuropraxia is LESS common - just under 1% - Iâ€™m looking at the nerves so know exactly where they are. In a more superficial #smaslift tension is placed on the tissues above the nerve so is more likely to create a temporary traction injury or be pinched in a stitch.

caption:
Dacrocystorhinostomy is the name for the surgical procedure used to correct watery eye. Watery eye is a very common condition which results from either an over production of tears, or reduced drainage of tears. Watery Eye can be a very distressing condition for those who suffer from it, as the constant tearing from their eyes can make others think they are weeping. Surgery can be carried out either under local anaesthetic with sedation, or general anaesthetic. It is usually carried out as day case surgery, although some patients prefer to stay overnight.

There are two surgical procedures used to treat watery eye, one is performed externally and one is performed internally. In the external procedure your surgeon will make a small incision in the side of your nose and operate through this whereas in the internal procedure the operation is carried out with the aid of an endoscope (a pencil thin camera) passed up the nostril.

You can find out more about Dacrocystorhinostomy on my website.

caption:
The secret to Kerastem advanced hair therapy lies in your own natural body fat, which is particularly rich in regenerative cells with stem cells capabilities. Restoring a fat and stem cell rich environment to the scalp creates a safe, powerful treatment for triggering growth and restoring lost hair.

But how does the Kerastem treatment actually work?

The treatment takes your own natural fat and regenerative stem cells which are then injected into the scalp. Around 200-300cc of fat is extracted by liposuction and broken down through enzymatic digestion, producing on average 5ml of regenerative cells which contain adipose derived mesenchymal stem cells. A small amount of fat, 10-20cc depending on centimetre square of the scalp to be treated is processed separately through purification and reinjected into the scalp along with the regenerative stem cells. There, they combine to provide a rich, fertile environment which regenerates and stimulates the scalp. 

Patients treated with Kerastem experience thicker and fuller hair and see new hair growth in balding and thinning areas.

To find out more about this treatment, feel free to get in touch.

Lash extensions should always be applied leaving a small gap between the eyelid and the lash extension, this is because the lash adhesive should never come into contact with the skin and placing the lash extensions too close to the skin can cause discomfort.

Patch testing ðŸš©
Never let a lash technician apply lash extension adhesive directly to your skin during a patch test!! ðŸš© 
A patch test should consist of a few lash extensions being applied directly to the natural lashes, the same way they would be applied during your lash appointment. Patch testing for lash extensions is not 100% conclusive as only a small amount of product is used.
